<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Abigaile</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-04-20 13:18:09</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I got one of these for a bard friend last night.  We brought gold, as we were afraid of losing the plat.<BR>
<BR>
- Griffennes spawn in NK and are around L27-29 usually.  Sometimes blue at 34 but often green.  Seems like sometimes there are only fawns around, killing a bunch of them might help (I do it sometimes, not sure if it really helps or not).<BR>
<BR>
- Charm drops are fairly random.  I get them frequently, so I usually shout the /loc after I already have one.<BR>
<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Doktoor Rocksteady</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-05-04 20:07:53</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>This is the easiest Lam piece for a young bard to get. As stated just shout in Unrest for looting rights to bracelet, its no drop. As for the charm, I killed these things solo at 22 all the time. Got a charm and put it on before i even knew it was for the quest. Here's what you do: Go to N Karana, find a  griffene, (they spawn near the tower). Hit Selos WITHOUT a drum (they are relatively slow). Then use bruscos to kite. Selo once, Brusco's 6 to 7 times, Selo's again, perfect 90 degree turn, Brusco's ...you get the idea. Just try not to run into any other griffs on the way. Takes about 7 minutes to kill one if you do it perfect and its pretty easy do. You'll get used to how loud the griff is and know how close it is so you can hit the most Bruscos (you are running straight with it behind you on normal screen view). Great way to lvl at 22 to 24 too since they are red. Make sure you are going 90 degrees on your turns too so you go in a square without zoning. Also, dont slow down until you've hit bruscos 2 times after the turn. Hope this helps.<BR>
<BR>
Dok<BR>
Working for peace on Vallon </font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
